+{"id": "bd-nsn-epic", "title": "PORT: ns_name_ntop / ns_name_pton DNS wire-format codec to core::resolv::dns", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T09:34:24.561174Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T09:34:24.561174Z", "description": "Lift the RFC 1035 DNS-name wire \u2194 presentation conversions out of glibc_internal_abi.rs into core::resolv::dns. ns_name_ntop (~85 lines) decodes uncompressed wire-format labels (length-prefixed) into dotted text with backslash escaping for special chars and \\DDD escaping for non-printable bytes. ns_name_pton (~110 lines) goes the reverse. Two separate inline impls exist (ns_name_ntop and __ns_name_ntop) that are subtly different \u2014 port to one shared core helper that both delegate to."}
